<local:BaseWindow x:Class="glFTPd_Commander.Windows.HelpWindow"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        xmlns:local="clr-namespace:glFTPd_Commander.Windows"
        Title="Help - glFTPd Commander" 
        Height="768" 
        Width="1024"
        ResizeMode="CanResize" WindowStartupLocation="CenterOwner">
    <ScrollViewer VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
        <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Padding="15" FontSize="14">
            <Run FontWeight="Bold" FontSize="16">glFTPd Commander - User Guide</Run>
            <LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
            Welcome to glFTPd Commander, a powerful GUI for managing your glFTPd server via FTP.
            <LineBreak/><LineBreak/>

            <Run FontWeight="Bold">Getting Started</Run><LineBreak/>
            1. Launch the application.<LineBreak/>
            2. Use Sites -> Connect to select a saved connection.<LineBreak/><LineBreak/>

            <Run FontWeight="Bold">Managing FTP Connections</Run><LineBreak/>
            • Sites -> Settings lets you add, edit, or remove connection profiles.<LineBreak/>
            • Connections are stored encrypted in ftpconfig.txt.<LineBreak/><LineBreak/>

            <Run FontWeight="Bold">Main Interface</Run><LineBreak/>
            • Left Tree: Displays users (active/deleted) and groups.<LineBreak/>
            • Right Panel: Shows user or group details based on selection.<LineBreak/>
            • There are two tabs in the right panel called User &amp; Group Info and Custom Commands.<LineBreak/>
            • Custom Commands tab have 20 buttons that can be configured and a commandline with a terminal like window below showing the output of sent commands.<LineBreak/>
            • Right click on a configured Custom Command button to remove the current setting.<LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
            
            <Run FontWeight="Bold">How Changes Are Applied</Run><LineBreak/>
            • Most fields in glFTPd Commander — such as user flags, tagline, group description, or login limits — are updated when the field <Run FontWeight="Bold">loses focus</Run>.<LineBreak/>
            • To apply your changes: click outside the field or press <Run FontStyle="Italic">Tab</Run> after editing.<LineBreak/>
            • If you don’t change focus, your update will <Run FontWeight="Bold">not</Run> be saved or sent to the FTP server.<LineBreak/><LineBreak/>

            <Run FontWeight="Bold">User Management</Run><LineBreak/>
            • Add User: Requires username, password, group, and IP.<LineBreak/>
            • Edit flags, ratios, logins, tagline, and IP restrictions.<LineBreak/>
            • Take/Give credits in MiB, GiB, or TiB.<LineBreak/>
            • Delete/Purge users with caution.<LineBreak/><LineBreak/>

            <Run FontWeight="Bold">Group Management</Run><LineBreak/>
            • Add Group: Define name and description.<LineBreak/>
            • Edit slots, max logins, comments, and description.<LineBreak/>
            • Promote/Demote admins or remove group entirely.<LineBreak/><LineBreak/>

            <Run FontWeight="Bold">Security</Run><LineBreak/>
            • SSL certs are validated and can be remembered via a prompt.<LineBreak/>
            • All connections are forced into using either explicit or implicit SSL.<LineBreak/><LineBreak/>

            <Run FontWeight="Bold">Tips</Run><LineBreak/>
            • ESC closes open views.<LineBreak/>
            • Icons: * SiteOp, + Admin, 🔒 Deleted users.<LineBreak/>
            • Hover for tooltips in most fields.<LineBreak/><LineBreak/>
            
            <Run FontWeight="Bold">Help</Run><LineBreak/>
            • View this window via Help -> User Guide.<LineBreak/>
            • Version details under Help -> About.<LineBreak/>
        </TextBlock>
    </ScrollViewer>
</local:BaseWindow>
